        <updateDate>2020-08-10T14:05:34Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Closing the College Hunger Gap Act of 2019</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Education (ED) to collect data on the&nbsp;food and housing insecurity of college students. </p> <p>Specifically, ED must add questions that measure rates of food and housing insecurity to the National Postsecondary Student Aid Study. In addition, ED must collect&nbsp;data on student eligibility under the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP, formerly known as the food stamp program).</p> <p>ED must also provide students with contact information for the state agency that administers SNAP in their state.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
